channel.title: Official 0x00sec Clothing. Hoodies and T-Shirts anyone?
channel.description: Hoodies are cool. 0x00sec is cool. You know what is even cooler? # 0x00sec Hoodies. We get it, you're a badass, and you love hacking + computers. But you would look even more badass with one of these bad boys. Do you want something more understated? Okay. We gotcha. Do you want a hoodie with a zip? Okay, you Aussie. [We got you covered too](https://shop.spreadshirt.com/0x00sec/0x00sec+rectangle+white+logo-A593d9f84f6c60d14d83544c7?department=1&productType=198&color=000000&appearance=2&view=2) Do you want something light? [Sweatshirt?](https://shop.spreadshirt.com/0x00sec/square+compact-A593da4a2aa0c6d5ff865e2ea?productType=512&appearance=2&appearance=2&productType=512) Got a dog? [Check it!](https://shop.spreadshirt.com/0x00sec/accessories) BUTTONS! # Pricing Okay, I'm not gonna mess you around here. They are expensive. Premium T-Shirts are $23.50 each, and the Premium Hoodies are almost $50. These are 80/20 blends (80% cotton, 20% polyester). There are cheaper versions however, the ordinary t-shirts are $18.49, and the ordinary hoodies are $35. They use a 'rougher' material which is 50/50 blend. In the clothing world, more cotton usually == softer. # Conclusion Say hello to the new shop at [swag.0x00sec.org](https://swag.0x00sec.org). This is Win-Win. You buy one of these, you look boss, you're warm, you get to show off your affiliation with the coolest up and coming Security network yet, and you also help support 0x00sec too; so everybody can continue learning and sharing for free. I can't wait to start seeing these littered around at DEFCON :stuck_out_tongue: \- pry0cc on behalf of 0x00sec.org ;) Keep nullin'
